{
  "texts": [
    "Substances such as salts, fats, and acids can influence basic taste modalities like sweetness, sourness, saltiness, bitterness, and umami.",
    "These interactions are often nonlinear and vary depending on concentration, context, and food composition.",
    "This complexity makes it difficult for AI models to predict sensory outcomes accurately.",
    "To address this issue, machine learning approaches need to process multiple types of input, including chemical data, sensory responses, and environmental conditions.",
    "Multimodal input processing allows the model to consider interactions that would otherwise be overlooked."
  ]
}